    "updated_at": "2016-09-20T15:33:14Z",
    "body": "You may have misunderstood me. To replicate my issue, add the following menu item to, say, the 'View' menu of the default app:\n\n``` js\n{\n  label: 'Blah',\n  accelerator: 'Up',\n  click() {\n    // Some code I want to execute if the user presses the up key\n  }\n}\n```\n\nThen run `remote.dialog.showOpenDialog(remote.getCurrentWindow())` in devtools of the default app and notice that the up arrow doesn't work for navigating inside the open file sheet.\n"
